Video Link Saver — Setup Guide
About

Video Link Saver is a fully offline Windows desktop application that helps users save, organize, and search YouTube and Instagram video links locally on their PC.

The application is:

Free to use
Open source
Offline-only
Privacy-focused
Lightweight and secure

All data is stored locally on your own device inside an Excel (.xlsx) file. No internet connection, cloud storage, tracking, or telemetry is used.

System Requirements
Windows 10 or Windows 11
64-bit Windows recommended
Minimum 4 GB RAM
Around 200 MB free storage space
Installation Instructions
Step 1 — Run the Setup File

Double-click:

VideoLinkSaverSetup.exe

If Windows SmartScreen appears:

Click More Info
Click Run Anyway

This happens because the installer is not code-signed yet.

Step 2 — Choose Installation Location

The default installation location is:

C:\Program Files\Video Link Saver

You may change it if desired.

Step 3 — Complete Installation

Follow the installer steps and click:

Next
Install
Finish

You can optionally create:

Desktop shortcut
Start menu shortcut
First Launch

When the application launches for the first time:

the required storage folder is created automatically,
the Excel database file is generated automatically,
dark/light theme settings are initialized.

No setup or account creation is required.

Data Storage Location

Your saved video links are stored locally at:

%LOCALAPPDATA%\VideoLinkSaver\the saves links.xlsx

Usually:

C:\Users\<YourName>\AppData\Local\VideoLinkSaver\the saves links.xlsx
Important Notes
Do not manually rename the Excel file while the app is running.
You may create backups of the Excel file for safety.
If the Excel file is deleted or corrupted, the app automatically recreates a new clean file.
Privacy & Security

Video Link Saver:

never uploads data,
never connects to online servers,
never tracks users,
never collects analytics,
works completely offline.

All saved information remains on your own computer.

Uninstalling

To uninstall:

Open Windows Settings
Go to Apps
Find “Video Link Saver”
Click Uninstall

Your Excel data file may remain on your PC unless deleted manually.

Open Source

This project is open source and free to use for personal and educational purposes.

Support

If you encounter issues:

rebuild the application using the source code,
reinstall the setup,
or restore your Excel backup file if needed.
